evs.data.fileio
Class GlobalUnitsReader

java.lang.Object
  evs.data.fileio.GlobalUnitsReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
StaticClassInitializer
public final class GlobalUnitsReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements StaticClassInitializer

Class comprising static methods for reading in global units, such as time systems and measurement units. All units should be stored in US English (e.g. METER not METRE). All methods should check that units have been read and should read otherwise by calling the constructor.

Version:
4.0
Author:
evs@hydrosolved.com

getMilliConversionFactor

public static double getMilliConversionFactor(java.lang.String units)
Returns the millisecond conversion factor for the specified input units. Approximations are used for months (30 days), years (365 days), decades (3650 days) and centuries (36500 days). The options for units are: MILLISECOND SECOND MINUTE HOUR DAY WEEK MONTH YEAR DECADE CENTURY

Parameters:
units - the time units
Returns:
the millisecond conversion factor
